title: The Everyl Brothers-audiophile vinyl rip, Rhino LP FLAC, metadat
description:
This is the All They Had To Do Was Dream LP on the Rhino label. This was made from the original master tapes and not only contains alternate (and usually slower paced) takes compared to the commercial releases, it also has studio patter between the brothers and the musisicans with the overall result being a very live and immediate feel. The recording quality is beyond good and makes you wonder what if any improvements have been made in the 50-odd years since this was recorded. 

The LP was transcribed using a Lyra Helikon SL cartridge and a $15,000 custom built all-tube phono stage
